    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely! If you see three sharps at the beginning of a piece of sheet music, you can use the circle of fifths to determine the key signature. Start at the C major point on the circle, which has no sharps or flats. Then, move clockwise one step to G major, which has one sharp. Move another step to D major, which has two sharps. Finally, move one more step to F major, which has three sharps. So, the key signature with three sharps is F major. Remember, the circle of fifths is like a map of key signatures, and by following the path of sharps and flats, you can find your way to any key signature. Just keep in mind that sometimes musicians might use accidentals to deviate from the circle, so it's always good to listen closely to the music and check if there are any unexpected notes.",
